                <event>
                    <head xml:lang="en">
                        Document image acquisition and processing
                    </head>
                    <desc xml:lang="en" corresp="definition">
                        Already before archiving, during the actual acquisition of images for RTI, relevant metadata and documentation should be collected. This can be done with e.g. a dedicated tabular protocol or shooting log. Minimal information should include description of the capture method including specific settings, the hardware used, persons involved, and object information such as an inventory number. After image acquisition all processing steps should also be recorded in the shooting log in order to provide for replicability.
                    </desc>
